cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.NI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the implementation and performance evaluation of a parallel programming model (OpenSHMEM) on a many-core architecture (Adapteva Epiphany) within a single-board computer (Parallella). 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper focuses on the Epiphany architecture and its network-on-chip. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is another possible category as the paper evaluates the performance of the OpenSHMEM implementation on the Epiphany architecture. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible category as the paper discusses the network-on-chip of the Epiphany architecture. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the implementation and evaluation of a programming model on a specific hardware system.
